net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api

Enum Solmization

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Enum<Solmization>
      • net.sf.mmm.music.datatype.api.Solmization
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, Comparable<Solmization>, Interval

    public enum Solmization
extends Enum<Solmization>
implements Interval
    Solmization is a system of attributing a distinct syllable to each note in a musical scale. In general there are different variants of solmization grown over history. However, the most interesting is the relative solmization that associates tones of a scale with syllables and is therefore independent of a MusicalKey.
    So for a major scale the Solmization order is DO, RE, MI, FA, SO, LA, TI. In C-major this would be equivalent to C, D, E, F, G, A, H.
    For a minor scale the Solmization order is LA, TI, DO, RE, MI, FA, SO. In A-minor this would be equivalent to A, H, C, D, E, F, G.
    Author:
    hohwille

      • getChromaticSteps

        public Integer getChromaticSteps(TonalSystem system)
        Returns the number of chromatic semitone steps from the initial TonePitch.
        ATTENTION:
        This means the result is 0-based, so e.g. for ChromaticInterval.PERFECT_FOURTH it will return 5.
        Specified by:
        getChromaticSteps in interface Interval
        Parameters:
        system - the underlying TonalSystem.
        Returns:
        the number of semitone steps relative to the initial TonePitch (tonika) or null if undefined (e.g. for Solmization if TonalSystem is null or in case of a DiatonicInterval). The modulo of eight (%12) of the result is the index of the TonePitch from the chromatic scale of the MusicalKey with the initial TonePitch as tonika).

      • getDiatonicSteps

        public Integer getDiatonicSteps(TonalSystem system)
        Returns the number of diatonic steps from the initial TonePitch.
        ATTENTION:
        This means the result is 0-based, so e.g. for DiatonicInterval.THIRD it will return 2 (NOT 3) and for DiatonicInterval.OCTAVE it will return 7 (NOT 8).
        Specified by:
        getDiatonicSteps in interface Interval
        Parameters:
        system - the underlying TonalSystem.
        Returns:
        the number of diatonic steps relative to the initial TonePitch (tonika) or null if undefined (e.g. for Solmization if TonalSystem is null). The modulo of eight (%8) of the result is the index of the TonePitch from the diatonic scale of the MusicalKey with the initial TonePitch as tonika).
